frameDefinitions: An Entity is in motion  at a particular Speed, a momentaneous description of distance traveled per time.
This describes a part_whole relationship where the Part provides the boundary between the Whole and what is not that object.
An Asset is in a state where it is exposed to or otherwise liable to be affected by a Harmful_event, which may be metonymically evoked by reference to a Dangerous_entity.
The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .
Generally without overall (translational) motion,  an Agent places a Theme at a location, the Goal, which is profiled.
Money is a medium used for exchanging goods and services.
frameExamples: We came to the southern <t><fex name='Part'>edge</fex></t>  of the town  .
If you are a farmer, you are at <t>risk</t> for hearing loss caused by noise exposure in your work.
The underwater sequences <t>warrant</t> the price of the admission alone.
David <t>placed</t> his briefcase on the floor.
The <t>money</t> for our daughter's college education is currently earning interest in a savings account.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> whose <fen>Speed</fen> is under consideration.

The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is a function of the distance that the <fen>Entity</fen> moves in a given duration. With the adjectives of this frame this Frame Element is generally incorporated.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Entity</fen>'s speed.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Speed</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Speed</fen>.
An undivided entity having all its <fen>Part</fen>s.
<fen>Part</fen> is that which forms a boundary between the <fen>Whole</fen> and what is not the object.
Something judged to be desirable or valuable which might be lost or damaged.
An action that may occur or a state which may hold which could result in the loss of or damage to the <fen>Asset</fen>.
A concrete or abstract entity which may come to cause the loss of, or damage to the <fen>Asset</fen> either due to its participation in a <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.
The time period during which the <fen>Asset</fen> enjoys  the specified level of security from a <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.

A particular location in which the <fen>Asset</fen> is secure. Frequently, it is to be inferred that the characteristics of the location protect the <fen>Asset</fen> from a potential <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.
An Eventuality or an Entity that is taken to constitute sufficient reason for taking another <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that is taken to be justifiable given the <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes location during the Placing.
The role <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up. This role is profiled by words in this frame.
<fen>Time</fen> is when the Placing occurs
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Placing occurs.
<fen>Money</fen> is used as a medium of exchange.
